                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            2.1.6 The Common European Framework of Reference (CEFR)
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            Teachers around the world use different terminology to refer to the level of English a student has achieved: you may hear descriptions of levels such as Starter, Beginner, Basic, Pre-Intermediate, Intermediate, Advanced, Proficient and any number of other variations on these. While an experienced teacher may intuitively understand these levels, a far more useful and structured way of understanding students' levels is to become familiar with The Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR).
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

